"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-2024-05-02-katie-ledecky-planning-compete-2028-olympics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"What does American swimming icon Katie Ledecky have left to prove?\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 66, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10, \"end\": 18, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9998663902473495, \"rank\": 0.00011209451297926192, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 33, \"end\": 46, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Not much.\", \"from\": 67, \"to\": 76, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her medal record is eye-popping: seven Olympics golds and three Olympic silvers to go with 21 world golds and five silvers.\", \"from\": 78, \"to\": 201, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She owns the world long- and short-course records in the 800-meter freestyle and 1500-meter freestyle.\", \"from\": 202, \"to\": 304, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"No conversation attempting to rank the greatest North American athletes of the 21st century is complete without her.\", \"from\": 305, \"to\": 421, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 359, \"end\": 367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9998663902473495, \"rank\": 0.00011209451297926192, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And yet, not only is Ledecky primed for another big Olympics this summer in Paris, she also indicated to NBC recently that she might not be done after that.\", \"from\": 423, \"to\": 579, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 499, \"end\": 504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999566890863035, \"rank\": 4.3312789573467326e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 528, \"end\": 531, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"score\": 0.9999980595071702, \"rank\": 1.6942504987230572e-06, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC_Sports\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The (2028) Olympics being in LA is very appealing.\", \"from\": 581, \"to\": 632, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not very many athletes get an opportunity to compete in a home Games,\\\" Ledeckysaid.\", \"from\": 633, \"to\": 716, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I definitely at this point am planning on going through 2028... whether I compete in one event, multiple events, a relay, whatever.\\\"\", \"from\": 717, \"to\": 850, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky turned 27 on St. Patrick's Day, and will be 31 by the time Los Angeles rolls around.\", \"from\": 852, \"to\": 944, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 877, \"end\": 884, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Drake\", \"score\": 0.6683183094991051, \"rank\": 0.4867582174832491, \"text\": \"Patrick\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Drake\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Drake\"}, {\"begin\": 919, \"end\": 930, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.99996682840464, \"rank\": 3.2943737000441395e-05, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only three women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094the United States's Dara Torres in 2000, the Netherlands' Inge de Bruijn in 2004, and West Germany's Ursula Happe in 1956\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094have ever won a swimming gold past the age of 30.\", \"from\": 945, \"to\": 1137, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 968, \"end\": 981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.7260250814612328, \"rank\": 0.37736104067840964, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 984, \"end\": 995, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dara_Torres\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dara Torres\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dara_Torres\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dara_Torres\"}, {\"begin\": 1009, \"end\": 1020, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9999879100817964, \"rank\": 6.233205357122454e-06, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 1050, \"end\": 1062, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/West_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9954829919614026, \"rank\": 0.003609920616823693, \"text\": \"West Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/West_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/West_Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 1065, \"end\": 1077, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ursula_Happe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ursula Happe\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ursula_Happe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ursula_Happe\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If there is anyone in swimming unbound by the sport's history, however, it's Ledecky.\", \"from\": 1139, \"to\": 1224, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Loading recommendations...\", \"from\": 1226, \"to\": 1252, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Patrick Andres is a staff writer on the Breaking and Trending News team at Sports Illustrated.\", \"from\": 1253, \"to\": 1411, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1317, \"end\": 1324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Drake\", \"score\": 0.6683183094991051, \"rank\": 0.4867582174832491, \"text\": \"Patrick\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Drake\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Drake\"}, {\"begin\": 1392, \"end\": 1410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 5.368285487891991e-13, \"text\": \"Sports Illustrated\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He joined SI in December 2022, having worked for The Blade, Athlon Sports, Fear the Sword and Diamond Digest.\", \"from\": 1412, \"to\": 1521, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Andres has covered everything from zero-attendance Big Ten basketball to a seven-overtime college football game.\", \"from\": 1522, \"to\": 1634, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He is a graduate of Northwestern University's Medill School of Journalism with a double major in history .\", \"from\": 1635, \"to\": 1741, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1655, \"end\": 1678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northwestern_University\", \"score\": 0.999995846724899, \"rank\": 4.030688943874879e-06, \"text\": \"Northwestern University\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northwestern_Univers